a movie library manager that uses json to store data
app.py that is used for website applications

made this to play around with json, then I wanted to try playing with making a website app

the app uses flask as the web server, when you fill out the form for adding a movie, browser sends it to flask, flask calls the function, function writes to the json file
and finally the page reloads with new movie added.

requirments
- Python 3.x
- Flask

flask is needed in order for the website to work

I created a virtual machine to hold flask
go to directory of this folder in the cmd
python -m venv venv or py -m venv venv

run this line to use the virtual environment
venv\Scripts\activate.bat

install flask
pip install flask

run app
python app.py
or
py app.py

open browser and go to
http://127.0.0.1:5000

to stop app, crtl + c
in the terminal

plz note:
- Movie data is saved automatically to `movies.json` in the project folder
- The file will be created on the first run
